frameDefinitions: Some Stimulus causes a Cognizer to think of a prior Phenomenon due to its perceived similarity.
A Selector, often an individual in a leadership role, appoints a Official to assume an official Role in an organization (which can be expressed as the Body).
Item-1 and Item-2 are compatible with each other if they can exist or function together in some context without problems, conflict, or other undesirable situation.
An Entity comes into existence at a particular Place and Time which may take a certain Duration_of_endstate, have a Cause, or be formed from Components.
A Speaker addresses an Addressee with a Message, which may be indirectly referred to as a Topic.
frameExamples: I burned down the malt shop where we used to go just because it <t>reminds</t> me of you
Press secretaries <t>accredit</t> journalists to the sessions.
The hand <t>around</t> the sword-hilt was no less impressive than the sword .
Make sure your site is <t>compatible</t> with any browser.
Problems may <t>arise</t> whenever an S1 sophont enters the game.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Cognizer</fen> is the person who remembers the <fen>Phenomenon</fen> .
The <fen>Phenomenon</fen> is the mental content that a <fen>Cognizer</fen> remembers.
The entity or situation that causes the <fen>Cognizer</fen> to think of the <fen>Phenomenon</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the Cognizer remembers the <fen>Phenomenon</fen>.
The <fen>Selector</fen> is responsible for the appointment of the new official.  Typically, it occurs as the External Argument of verbs.
The <fen>Official</fen> is a person appointed to a recognized position.

Frequently, the <fen>Official</fen> is referred to only by his/her role. However, the <fen>Role</fen> can be expressed separately from the leader, usually as either a secondary predicate or in a PP Complement (headed by <m>as</m>).
The <fen>Function</fen> is the purpose the <fen>Official</fen> will fufill.
A group of individuals who are elected or appointed to perform some function, and to which the <fen>Official</fen> is assigned.
When the designation of the official takes place.
Where the appointment takes place.
The <fen>Figure</fen> is the entity located with respect to the <fen>Ground</fen>.
The <fen>Ground</fen> is the area that the <fen>Figure</fen> surrounds.
The area or zone immediately external to the <fen>Ground</fen>.  This role excludes <fen>Figure</fen> and is only used in particular constructions such as the following:
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Figure</fen> is located around the <fen>Ground</fen>.
The Frame Element <fen>Item_1</fen> marks the grammatically more prominent of the two entities, i.e.the subject in active clauses, when they are expressed separately.
The Frame Element <fen>Item_2</fen> marks the grammatically less prominent of the <fen>Items</fen> when they are expressed separately.
This role is used when the <fen>Items</fen> are expressed jointly in a phrase, either a plural or a coordinated NP.
This Frame Element is used for expressions that indicate a <fen>Parameter</fen> or respect in which the <fen>Items</fen> are said to be compatible, not in conflict.
Concrete or abstract entity that did not exist before the <fen>Time</fen> of the event.
This role identifes the Time when a new Entity comes into existence.
This is the Place where the new Entity comes into being.
The <fen>Speaker</fen> is the sentient entity that produces the <fen>Message</fen>.
The <fen>Addressee</fen> receives the <fen>Message</fen> from the <fen>Speaker</fen>.
The <fen>Message</fen> is the communication produced by the <fen>Speaker</fen>.
The <fen>Topic</fen> is a general description of the content of the <fen>Message</fen>.
This role is the <fen>Medium</fen> in which the <fen>Message</fen> is expressed.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Speaker</fen> informs the <fen>Addressee</fen> of the <fen>Message</fen>.
<fen>Place</fen> is the location in which the <fen>Speaker</fen> informs  the <fen>Addressee</fen> of the <fen>Message</fen>.

The two applications are compatible <fex>in their essential features</fex>.

out great.
